# Decide the Session-Start Briefing Contract

## Question

What does every agent wake up knowing? The rhizomatic briefing (claude
SessionStart hook) currently carries shallow session metadata. Decide: how
many observations and at what grain (today's index + N most-relevant atoms?
scoped to the session's repo/cwd?), ranking (recency vs relevance vs
graph-adjacency), staleness rule (durable decision pages outrank stale
observations — the temporal-gradient conflict rule, validated day one),
token budget per briefing, sensitive handling (include locally?), and WHICH
surfaces get it: claude hook, pi APPEND/extension, codex AGENTS — same
content everywhere or per-runtime shaping?
